<metadata><name>2026 SRS Trip Plan - Alt D (reverse, BTR split, V1)</name><desc>Day-split tracks (reverse direction, BTR split), POIs, and camps for Alt D (Variant V1).</desc><time>2026-04-16T00:00:00Z</time></metadata>
<wpt lat="40.772616" lon="-113.981099"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY] May 1 (Fri) - Meet + Bonneville overnight - Bonneville Salt Flats — leading candidate (dispersed, TBD)</name><desc>Typically free on BLM desert pull-offs — verify postings | None — pack out waste; respect wet salt | Leading overnight candidate for the group scout. Confirm legal dispersed rules and salt moisture before driving on flats. | Access: NW of Wendover; reach via I-80 corridor.</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="40.80273" lon="-114.00395"><name>[CAMP BACKUP] May 1 (Fri) - Meet + Bonneville overnight - Bonneville Salt Flats — alternate pin</name><desc>Typically free — verify postings | None | Second Bonneville-area candidate; use if primary cluster is occupied or soggy. | Access: Same general Bonneville / Wendover approach.</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="42.14688" lon="-113.08988"><name>[CAMP LAST-RESORT] May 1 (Fri) - Meet + Bonneville overnight - Northern corridor bailouts (NOT Bonneville)</name><desc>Varies | None | Only if the group reroutes far north (e.g. I-84 toward Sublett / Idaho). NOT substitutes for Bonneville — companion pin ~42.13773, -113.07632. | Access: Off corridor north of the Bonneville overnight plan.</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.65606" lon="-110.66015"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY] May 2 (Sat) - Travel + Stage (Temple Mtn side) - Temple Mountain Townsite - Site 1 (Group Site) (GPX)</name><desc>$50/night | Vault toilets, fire rings, tables, large shade structure | Group-capacity site; first-come only. Tuesday night very likely open. Used Friday May 1 night as staging for reverse-direction alternates. | Access: Temple Mtn Rd, Townsite Campground complex</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6577" lon="-110.66224"><name>[CAMP BACKUP] May 2 (Sat) - Travel + Stage (Temple Mtn side) - Temple Mount East Campground (GPX)</name><desc>$15/site | Vault toilets | 10-site loop, first-come. Split group across several sites if group site is taken. | Access: Temple Mtn Rd, E of the Townsite</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.5734" lon="-110.703"><name>[CAMP LAST-RESORT] May 2 (Sat) - Travel + Stage (Temple Mtn side) - Goblin Valley SP (reservable individual sites)</name><desc>$35-40/night | Toilets, water, showers | Reservation strongly recommended on weekends. Use when Temple Mtn FCFS sites are full on arrival Friday night. | Access: Hwy 24 -&gt; Goblin Valley Rd W</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.872668" lon="-110.787818"><ele>2135.0</ele><name>DP - Dutchman Arch</name><sym>stone</sym></wpt>
