<wpt lat="38.666217" lon="-110.6478182"><ele>1607.0</ele><name>DP - North Temple Wash</name><desc>Scenic narrows drive-through</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6503198742" lon="-110.6760708959"><ele>1599.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Wild Horse Canyon</name><desc>AllTrails Wild Horse Canyon trail; lower priority — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.661013" lon="-110.669472"><ele>1633.0</ele><name>DP - Temple Wash Petroglpyphs</name><desc>Roadside panel (GPX name has a typo, kept exact for lookup)</desc><sym>petroglyph</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.653784" lon="-110.676269"><ele>1722.0</ele><name>[HIKE] DP - Wild Horse Window Arch</name><desc>Default Day 3 hike; route author #1 geology; 2 mi RT; BLM not GSVP gate; set up camp before this hike and carpool to the trailhead; see slot-canyon-guide.html + AllTrails WHW</desc><sym>stone</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.643607" lon="-110.745181"><ele>1678.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Crack Canyon Trailhead</name><desc>Crack Canyon hike parking; camping nearby possible — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>known-route</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6323158128" lon="-110.7394259487"><ele>1632.0</ele><name>[HIKE] DP - Crack Canyon</name><desc>Tactical slot; ~5 mi RT typical (Utah.com); ~10 ft drop ~1 mi in; see slot-canyon-guide.html + AllTrails Crack Canyon Wilderness</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.629651" lon="-110.763442"><ele>1567.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Chute Canyon Trailhead</name><desc>Chute Canyon hike parking — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>known-route</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6187227373" lon="-110.7610813765"><ele>1538.0</ele><name>[HIKE] DP - Chute Canyon</name><desc>Tactical slot/wash; easier; wide ~first mi; ~0.8 mi to first narrowing (GCT); partial OAB typical; see slot-canyon-guide.html + AllTrails Crack Canyon Wilderness</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.64423" lon="-110.73771"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Temple Mtn -&gt; Sinbad -&gt; BTR W -&gt; Crack camp - Dispersed Camping near Crack Canyon trailhead</name><desc>Free (BLM) | None (no toilets, no water) | Signed BLM dispersed camping pocket. First-come; scout on arrival. Daylight arrival strongly preferred. | Access: Behind-the-Reef Rd S of Crack Canyon TH</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6461" lon="-110.7339"><name>[CAMP BACKUP] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Temple Mtn -&gt; Sinbad -&gt; BTR W -&gt; Crack camp - Crack Canyon Trailhead (pockets near TH)</name><desc>Free (BLM) | None | Small pullouts within walking distance of the Crack Canyon TH. Useful backup if the main dispersed pocket fills. | Access: Crack Canyon TH road spur</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.66" lon="-110.73253"><name>[CAMP LAST-RESORT] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Temple Mtn -&gt; Sinbad -&gt; BTR W -&gt; Crack camp - Camp Site waypoint (38.66000, -110.73253)</name><desc>Free (BLM) | None | GPX &quot;Camp&quot; waypoint ~1.8 km N of the primary; last-resort if both closer options are full or unworkable. Scout before splitting the group. | Access: Behind-the-Reef Rd</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6078020911" lon="-110.792877126"><ele>1645.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Little Wild Horse Slot Canyon</name><desc>Full LWH/Bell loop waypoint only; same caveats — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6149456972" lon="-110.8025986551"><ele>1673.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Little Wild Horse Canyon Trail</name><desc>LWH/Bell TH; skip OAB from Behind-the-Reef unless full ~8 mi LWH/Bell loop + party OK scrambling; FLASH FLOOD RISK — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>known-route</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6174483344" lon="-110.8121358239"><ele>1733.0</ele><name>DP - Behind the Reef trail</name><desc>Technical trail section - slow</desc><sym>off-road</sym></wpt>
