<wpt lat="38.57563" lon="-109.52401"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY] May 6 (Wed) - Split at Wedge; stay-overs I-70 E to Moab - Sand Flats Recreation Area — adjacent FCFS sites (cluster)</name><desc>Day-use pass + per-night camping fee (pay fee station) | Picnic tables, fire rings, pit toilets; no drinking water onsite | No group reservation: plan to snag several adjoining sites on the same loop (or nearby loops) so the crew stays visual distance. Typical rule is up to two vehicles parked at a numbered site **when everything fits**—put tow rigs/trailers on their own pads when tandem parking is tight. Spring Thu–Sat nights fill quickly; aim to arrive midday when possible. | Access: From Moab: 400 East -&gt; Mill Creek Dr -&gt; Sand Flats Rd to BLM/co-county booth</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.471" lon="-109.745"><name>[CAMP BACKUP] May 6 (Wed) - Split at Wedge; stay-overs I-70 E to Moab - Dead Horse Point SP - Wingate (electric site)</name><desc>$60/night | Electric, vault toilets, no showers | 150+ sites available May 6. One site fits up to 8. | Access: Hwy 313 W off Hwy 191</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.65" lon="-109.77"><name>[CAMP LAST-RESORT] May 6 (Wed) - Split at Wedge; stay-overs I-70 E to Moab - BLM designated dispersed pods (Mill Canyon / Cotter / Dubinky)</name><desc>Free where signed — human-waste containment required | No services; numbered posts — see BLM map | ~11–22 mi from Moab depending on spur. Camp only signed sites. | Access: Hwy 191 / SR 313 corridors north/northwest</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
